mainmatter.p:
The Karoubi envelope of a category \mathbb{C}, written \mathsf{Split} ( \mathbb{C} ), is the
category whose

      objects are pairs of the form (C, e) where C is an object of
      \mathbb{C} and e : C  \to  C is an idempotent of C;

      morphisms are triples (e, f, e') : (C, e)  \to  (C', e') where f
      : C  \to  C' is a morphism of \mathbb{C} satisfying e'  \circ  f = f = f
       \circ  e;

      composition operation is taken directly from \mathbb{C};

      identity morphisms on objects (C, e) are given by (e, e, e).
